│ THOUGHT: Let me try to understand the issue by looking at what the correct behavior should be. The problem is that the transformation assumes that srem(C1*X, C2*X) can be simplified when C1 and C2 are       │
│ constants, but this is not valid for signed remainder when X can be negative.                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The specific case here is:                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ - C1 = 128 (from shl X, 7)                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ - C2 = 127 (from mul X, 127)                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ For X = -1:                                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ - C1*X = -128                                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ - C2*X = -127                                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ - srem(-128, -127) = -1                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ But the transformation gives -X = 1.                                                                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The root cause is likely a simplification rule that doesn't properly handle the signed nature of the remainder operation. In LLVM, srem follows the dividend's sign, so srem(a, b) has the same sign as a.     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Let me try one more approach to find the relevant code. Maybe the main InstCombine logic is in a file called "InstCombine.cpp" or "InstructionCombine.cpp".                                                    │
